title: ASX poised to rise to end best month since 1988
summary: Australian shares are set to open higher on the final day of the month, bolstered by further gains in New York, as well as a renewed rally in iron ore and oil.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to open lower as global trading pauses
summary: Australian shares are set to open down after light trading led to modest losses in Europe. US markets are closed for the Thanksgiving holiday.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to slip, Wall St pauses after records reset
summary: Australian shares are set to open lower, as Wall Street investors opted to de-risk heading into the Thanksgiving break.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Dow tops 30,000 for first time
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, bolstered by a renewed rally in New York as political uncertainty continues to ease in Washington. Tesla rallied.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Dow keeps 30,000 in sight, Tesla extends rally
summary: Australian shares are poised to rise at the open, bolstered by further gains on Wall Street. Tesla nears another market cap marker.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, global economic data in focus
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher as the risks associated with South Australia's short-lived lockdown ease.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, US stocks close higher
summary: Australian shares poised to open higher. Wall Street shrugged off early losses to edge up on hopes stimulus talks may be revived.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall after late Wall St slide
summary: Australian shares are poised to open lower after Wall Street shares sold off late in the session amid concerns surging virus cases will prompt wider lockdowns.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Wall St eases after record reset
summary: Australian shares are set to open modestly higher as the Moderna vaccine euphoria tempered. Gold, oil eased. $A slips.
author: Timothy Moore

title: Dow closes at record high with 30,000 within reach
summary: The Dow Jones Industrial Average closed at a record high as investors saw Moderna's vaccine trial news as another sign of light at the end of the COVID-19 tunnel.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, extending last week's rally
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher as investors look through rising US virus cases for better economic prospects in 2021.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to fall, Wall St drops on US virus surge
summary: Australian shares are set to open lower, following the lead of global equities, as grim US virus data checks optimism that a vaccine is near at hand.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, techs bounce in New York
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, as Wall Street regained its tech footing. $A slips. US bond market closed for Veterans' Day.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, pace of global rotation slows
summary: Australian shares are poised to extend their advance. Wall Street is mixed. Oil, gold higher. $A flat.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to soar 2.1pc at open on vaccine news
summary: Australian shares are poised to leap at the open, amid a global relief rally. Oil surged, gold plunged, US bond yields shot higher.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX set to rise, Wall Street hits pause
summary: Australian shares are poised to open modestly higher, with miners positioned to advance on a weaker US dollar as a divided US government comes into focus.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, Nasdaq reaches for record high
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, bolstered by a broad Wall Street rally. $A surges more than 1pc.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, investors reposition for status quo
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, following rallies in Europe and New York, amid expectations neither Trump nor Biden, whoever prevails, will not have a decisive mandate.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to edge higher, Wall St rallies, $A surges
summary: Australian shares are poised for a modest opening gain. Shares advance in Europe and in New York. $A leaps higher.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, RBA poised to cut interest rates
summary: Australian shares are poised to rise modestly at the open, bolstered by manufacturing data in Europe and the US. $A steady.
author: Timothy Moore

title: ASX to rise, but could be muted by week of risks
summary: Australian shares are poised to open higher, though they could be checked by a long list of risks, including an expected RBA rate cut and the US election.
author: Timothy Moore
